The Vice President, Mike Pence, addressed the National Governors Association at the Naval Observatory in Washington, D.C. He thanked the governors for their leadership and spoke about the importance of state-based innovation and federalism. Pence pledged that the Trump administration is committed to working with the governors to rebuild America's infrastructure and economy. He also highlighted the governors' leadership during times of crisis, including natural disasters and mass shootings. Pence stated that the administration will work with the governors to prioritize school safety and find ways to prevent future attacks. He mentioned the actions already taken by the President, such as strengthening background checks and raising the age for purchasing certain firearms. Pence encouraged the governors to share their ideas and participate in discussions on school safety. He expressed confidence that with the governors' leadership and President Trump in the White House, they can find solutions for the American people.